{"type":"message","id":"674177c9","parentId":"e3e48543","timestamp":"2026-02-08T06:58:38.027Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! OpenClaw is running with PID 78806, and I can see that your Telegram message was successfully received, which means the connection to Telegram is now working properly with the proxy configuration.\n\nLet me summarize what we did to fix the issue:\n\n1. We identified that the Telegram plugin was failing to connect due to network restrictions requiring a VPN proxy\n2. We attempted to configure proxy settings in the OpenClaw config file, but discovered that \"network\" wasn't a valid configuration key\n3. We removed the invalid configuration and instead used environment variables to route all network traffic through your proxy at 127.0.0.1:7897\n4. We restarted OpenClaw with the proper proxy environment variables (HTTPS_PROXY, HTTP_PROXY, ALL_PROXY)\n\nNow your Telegram bot is able to communicate with the Telegram servers through your proxy, and the \"setMyCommands failed: Network request for 'setMyCommands' failed!\" error should be resolved.\n\nEverything appears to be working correctly now. Is there anything else you'd like me to help you with regarding your OpenClaw setup?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qwen-portal","model":"coder-model","usage":{"input":337,"output":230,"cacheRead":28864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29431,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1770533912425}}
